SERVICE CLOUD
Delete a Contact Center

You can delete a contact center from your Salesforce org. To delete a contact center, you must delete the voice calls associated with the contact center.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To delete a contact center:	Customize Application and Manage Call Centers

This feature is available with these telephony models:
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

WARNING
Deleting a contact center from a production org deletes the underlying Amazon Connect instance and all related assets.
Deleting a contact center from a sandbox org deletes associated Salesforce resources but not AWS artifacts.

To delete a contact center:
From Setup, enter Contact Centers in Quick Find.
Select Amazon Contact Centers or Partner Telephony Contact Centers.
Click the dropdown to the right of the contact center and select Delete.
title: Deleting a Contact Center in Salesforce
